==Description== <!--T:3-->

New concept of Cable Light Point Preset and SuppLines child object: <span style="color:blue;">introduced in version 0.3.0</span>

<!--T:4-->
The [[Image:Cables_CableLightPoint.svg|24px]] [[Cables_CableLightPoint|Cable Light Point]] creates a parametric light point object. The light point is a simple ring symbolizing the point where a cable exits from e.g. the wall to connect a light source (e.g. a lamp). It has default size upon creation, but some parameters, like '''Diameter''', '''Height''' or '''Thickness''' can be changed later. The '''Cable Light Point''' belongs to the [[Arch_Component|Arch Component]] class and inherits all of its properties. The '''Cable Light Point''' has [[Cables_SuppLines|SuppLines]] child object with two crosses. Each [[Cables_SuppLines|SuppLines]] cross can be used as attachment supports for cable passing through the ring. [[Cables_SuppLines|SuppLines]] object is not a part of Cable Light Point shape, it is a separate child object also visible in the [[Tree_View|Tree View]].

<!--T:6-->
'''Cable Light Point''' object can be colored by attaching desired [[Arch_SetMaterial|Material]] to the '''Material''' property.

